    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thurston</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawaiian Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With farther reference to the alleged violation
                    of the United States neutrality laws by Captain Martin of the schooner <hi
                        rend="italic">Wahlberg</hi>, I have the honor to inform you that I have
                    received from Mr. Wilder, Hawaiian consul at San Francisco, a further statement
                    concerning the witnesses. He states that he has found a deck hand of the tug
                    alleged to have delivered the arms on board of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Wahlberg</hi>, who makes a clear and direct statement, making a valuable
                    witness. He further states that the cook and mate of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Wahlberg</hi> were discharged from the <hi rend="italic">Wahlberg</hi> upon
                    her recent arrival at San Diego, and are now in San Francisco; also, that all of
                    these men are liable to ship on outgoing vessels at an early date, so that if
                    their evidence is to be obtained it will have to be soon, or it will become
                    unavailable.</p>
                <p>With renewed assurances, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. A. Thurston.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
